'''Lizbet Martínez'''{{sfn|Horowitz|Suchlicki|2003|p=321}} is a [[Cuba]]n [[violin]]ist and [[English (subject)|English]] teacher at [[M.A. Milam K-8 Center]].{{sfn|Tester|2010}}

During the "[[Balseros (rafters)|"balsero crisis"]] of 1994, over 30,000 Cubans immigrated to the United States from Cuba on rafts.{{sfn|Torres|2014}} Seen as a symbol of the balsero exodus, Martínez first became known on August 21, 1994, as a 12-year-old rafter from Cuba.{{sfn|Santiago|2014}}{{sfn|"In their own words"|2004}} This was when the [[U.S. Coast Guard]] picked her and her family out of her raft.{{sfn|"Violin remains key"|2003}} The Coast Guard wanted to take her violin because they thought the case might contain a weapon. She then opened the case and started to play [[The Star Spangled Banner]] on her violin.{{sfn|Marquez|1994}} She spent five months at the [[Guantanamo Bay Naval Base]] before being relocated to [[Miami, Florida|Miami]].{{sfn|Zucco|2003}}{{sfn|Davison|1995}}

Martínez attended [[Florida International University]] and received a [[Bachelor of Science]] degree in music education.{{sfn|De Valle|2003}} At her graduation at [[Florida International University]] she played the anthem in front of her fellow graduates to kick off the university's commencement ceremony.{{sfn|Diaz|2003}} Martínez later played on her violin in front of [[United States]] Presidents [[Bill Clinton]] and [[George W. Bush]].{{sfn|Zucco|2003}}{{sfn|Richter|1995}}{{sfn|Kelly|1995}} Martínez also performed alongside [[Gloria Estefan]] and [[Jon Secada]].{{sfn|Marquez|2001}}

She later became a teacher at Emerson Elementary, before teaching at M.A. Milam K-8 Center.{{sfn|Tester|2010}}{{sfn|Lamas|2003}} She taught music, until budget cuts took away Milam's music program, leading her to teach English. Martínez is also married and has two children.{{sfn|Torres|2014}} Martínez was also featured in the film ''Voices from Cuba''.{{sfn|"The Voices"|n.d.}} After 20 years passed since Martínez emigrated from Cuba, a follow-up article was published about the situation.{{sfn|Torres|2014}}

